# If you prefer the allow list template instead of the deny list, see community template:
# https://github.com/github/gitignore/blob/main/community/Golang/Go.AllowList.gitignore
#
# Binaries for programs and plugins
*.exe
*.exe~
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Test binary, built with `go test -c`
*.test

# Code coverage profiles and other test artifacts
*.out
coverage.*
*.coverprofile
profile.cov

# Dependency directories (remove the comment below to include it)
# vendor/

# Helm sub-chart tarballs are fetched on demand from Chart.lock; do
# not commit them. Chart.lock itself IS committed so installs stay
# reproducible without hitting chart repos on every PR.
helm/*/charts/

# Local docker build context — Dockerfile expects the binary to be
# already in the build directory (.docker-context/), populated by
# CI / dev scripts. Both files are reproducible from `go build` +
# `cp Dockerfile`, so they don't belong in git.
.docker-context/

# Go workspace file
go.work
go.work.sum

# env file
.env

# Editor/IDE
# .idea/
# .vscode/

# KubeAtlas generated artifacts
output/*
!output/.gitkeep
bin/
# goreleaser output (repo-root only — don't catch web/dist or
# cmd/kubeatlas/web/dist).
/dist/

# Embedded Web UI bundle. The directory is populated only at release
# time (Dockerfile / goreleaser before-hook) when building with
# -tags embed_web. Default builds skip the embed entirely, so nothing
# from this tree should be tracked. kubectl-atlas embeds the same
# bundle for its --local-ui mode.
cmd/kubeatlas/web/dist/
cmd/kubectl-atlas/web/dist/

# Docusaurus build artifacts
docs/.docusaurus/
docs/build/
docs/node_modules/
